two days of the conference will consider law and neuroscience issues as they arise throughout the human lifespan beginning friday morning with prenatal and infant brains and ending saturday afternoon with the neuroscience of aging and death about registration this event is open to the public registration is complimentary but required click here to rsvp questions for more information about this event click here if you have any questions contact andrea frey at freya uchastings edu sponsored by uc hastings college of law stanford law school hastings law journal ucsf uc hastings consortium on law science & health policy stanford center for law and the biosciences and the stanford center on longevity category uncategorized comments rss 2.0 feed trackback url leave a reply click here to cancel reply name required mail will not be published required website recent posts dr david relman on avian flu and national security video are hospitals gouging the uninsured video from stanford conference on law & the developing brain have we reached the end of alzheimer's law and policy of the developing brain neuroscience from womb to death clb workshop jaime king on prenatal genetic diagnosis and selective abortion clb workshop adam kolber on smooth and bumpy laws first light for human embryonic stem cell therapies the supreme court new technologies and privacy another case of approach avoidance clb workshop robin feldman on patent aggregators search by author clb people hank greely mark lemley nita farahany matt lamkin clb alumni teneille brown kelly lowenberg cj murdoch emily murphy brenda simon dov greenbaum guest bloggers ryan calo libby greismann jennifer hableib vinita kailasanath jane kim pages clb home page clb people conferences events newsletter archive subscribe follow clb on twitter join our mailing list subscribe to our rss feed search the blog search for search by month select month march 2012 february 2012 january 2012 december 2011 november 2011 october 2011 september